Introduction

Jung Ji-so is a South Korean actress and member of the project girl group WSG Wannabe.

She is best known for her roles in the drama "Imitation" as Maha, a member of the fictional girl group TEAPARTY and award-winning film "Parasite" which won the Palme d'Or at the Cannes Film Festival and the Academy Award for Best Picture.
